running at an annual rate of 1361 billion 20 percent below the 
alltime high imbalance of 1703 billion recorded last year 
presidentelect bush cited this improvement during the 
presidential campaign as proof that the reagan administrations 
policies of solving the countrys trade woes were working 
the administration launched an effort in september 1985 to drive 
the value of the dollar lower to make american goods more 
competitive on overseas markets while driving up the price of 
imports 
