when it opened it was a blue and white miracle in 
concrete and steel built in a civic frenzy to bring major league 
sports to the south 
twentythree years later atlantafulton county stadium finds 
itself a pariah among ballparks a place that both its tenants 
baseballs braves and footballs falcons are desperately trying to 
flee even before the mortgage is paid off 
grumbling about the stadium has gone on for years 
the round configuration isnt perfect for baseball and for 
football everyone agrees its worse when the rectangular field 
is fitted in beneath the circular stands the usually desirable 
50yardline seats are farthest away from the action 
dirty concourses and disgusting restrooms led some in recent 
years to dub it atlantafilthy county stadium the quality of 
