<TEXT>
furor over a film about christ corporate 
turmoil and a paralyzing strike troubled the movie world in 1988 
but it was a year of record prosperity and cautious optimism about 
the future 
major attractions in the holiday market guarantee that film 
grosses will pass last years record of 485 billion after a 
roaring summer and a slight dip after labor day ticket sales boomed 
over the thanksgiving weekend with such movies as scrooged 
oliver and company and the land before time 
two comedies the naked gun and twins the drama rain 
man and other december offerings will help swell the years total 
demonstrating anew that america has an almost insatiable appetite 
for movie entertainment 
but not everything in hollywood was coming up roses several film 
companies that expanded their output when movies started booming 
five years ago have now run into trouble 
delaurentiis entertainment group new world pictures and the 
cannon group suffered heavy losses and were struggling to survive 
after venturing disastrously into feature films lorimar 
telepictures hit the skids and merged into warner bros 
two of the greatest names of film history the merged mgmua 
underwent a turbulent year losing its production heads producers 
burt sugarman jon peters and peter guber tried to buy a portion of 
the company as did the sony corp both deals collapsed by years 
end the fate of mgmua was still in limbo 
the merger of tristar pictures and columbia pictures into a 
single entity columbia pictures entertainment was also in an 
unsettled state the company suffered a 104 million loss earlier 
this year mostly in movie writedowns losses from movies that are 
not released on schedule 
cocacola which owns 49 percent of the new company was rumored 
to be seeking an exit from the movie business 
the last temptation of christ martin scorseses film about 
what might have happened if jesus had survived the cross caused an 
uproar that is still being played out around the world religious 
fundamentalists staged a huge rally at universal studios urging the 
company to withdraw the film on grounds that it was sacrilege 
because the movie features a dream sequence in which jesus makes 
love to mary magdelene 
universal remained firm and the last temptation did fair 
business hampered by the refusal of some theater chains to book it 
the controversy continues as the film moves abroad greece is the 
latest country to ban it 
having barely avoided a directors strike last year hollywood 
producers were struck by the writers guild of america in 1988 the 
strike lasted 22 weeks and ended with a virtual standoff feature 
production did not seem slowed by the walkout but the opening of 
the 198889 television season was postponed 
the colorizing of blackandwhite vintage movies continued to 
rile movie buffs as well as the directors guild of america and its 
members but they could do nothing to stop the televising of tinted 
versions of casablanca boom town and other classics ted 
turner who owns the biggest supply of old movies even threatened 
to colorize orson welles 1941 classic citizen kane 
the last emperor was the big winner at the academy awards 
picking up oscars for best picture and for bernardo bertoluccis 
direction but for none of the actors the performance awards went 
to cher moonstruck michael douglas wall street sean 
connery the untouchables and olympia dukakis moonstruck 
the onceailing walt disney co proved to be the years success 
story with such attractions as three men and a baby good 
morning vietnam and who framed roger rabbit disney deposed 
paramount as the topgrossing studio capturing 20 percent of the 
market 
at years end disney announced formation of hollywood pictures 
the studios third movie production company to beef up its output 
of feature films the new company is scheduled to start up feb 1 
and to be making 12 movies a year within three years 
the new division was conceived as the most efficient way to 
produce more movies to fill a void left by the failure of some 
competitors and cuts at others 
not only did hollywood find comfort in theater business but the 
cassette market also continued to boom as evidenced by the 
longawaited release of et the extraterrestrial mcas first 
shipment was a record 106 million units that was more than twice 
as many as the previous record holder disneys cinderella 
</TEXT>
