<TEXT>
if projections by the nations train air and 
bus lines are any indication more americans than ever will be 
traveling during the christmas and new years holidays in 1988 
greyhound the nations largest intercity bus line says it will 
carry 134 million passengers between dec 18 and jan 3 or 10 
percent more than the 12 million people transported during the 
holidays last year 
in part the bus line attributes the increase to a recent boost 
in air fares and the limited availability of discountpriced seats 
on the nations major airlines said greyhound chief executive 
officer fred g currey who was in cleveland on tuesday to meet with 
company employees 
airplane ticket prices are very substantially higher this year 
and they are a factor currey told reporters and bus fares are 
very moderately priced 
curreys contention was disputed by organizations representing 
airlines and the nations travel agents 
most people buying at christmas bought their tickets weeks and 
months ago before fares went up said philip g davidoff 
