in other recent developments 
stratton mountain in vermont spent 45 million to install the 
largest ski lift in the country a 12passenger gondola able to 
carry 2400 people an hour 
burke mountain in east burke vt is making more than 1 
million in improvements to the 25yearold ski area including 
construction of 100 condominiums and a 20 percent expansion of 
snowmaking capabilities 
shawnee peak in bridgton maine is spending about 12 million 
to stimulate a moneylosing operation by adding new lifts rental 
equipment more lodge space and lights that will make it the largest 
night skiing resort in new england 
after a 15 million overhaul ski adventure in ashby mass is 
expected to reopen in december six years after the old mount 
watatic ski area went bankrupt and closed 
the 185 ski areas in the northeast led the nation in expansion 
this year spending 609 million on improvements compared with 56 
million spent by rocky mountain resorts and 51 million in far west 
ski areas according to the national ski areas association in 1987 
northeast ski areas spent 921 million 2 times the 1985 level 
last year the eight states in the northeast reported about 15 
million skier visits compared with 17 million in the rockies in 
the 198485 season attendance was less than 12 million in the east 
the east has a basic topographic disadvantage because its tallest 
mountains are less than half the size of the 10000 to 12000foot 
peaks found in the rockies mount washington in new hampshire is the 
regions tallest mountain at 6200 feet 
the rockies also offer complete resort areas with open skiing in 
wide snowy fields in new england most trails are cut through 
woods and ski areas are typically limited to lodges and have few 
other recreational opportunities 
to meet the competition new england skiing associations have 
expanded on a national campaign lets go skiing america by 
pushing for vacations at local resorts and trying to broaden modest 
increases in attendance over the last two years 
its not because theyre losing market share to the caribbean 
or some nonski service said phil camp executive director of the 
new england ski areas council an industry group the rate of 
growth of the consumer market in skiing has not been rapid like it 
was 15 or 18 years ago 
in vermont ski areas are teaming up to make the states resorts 
a destination one new program allows interchangable lift tickets at 
smugglers jay peak bolton and sugarbush 
the vermont ski areas association this year also began 
coordinating flydrive packages from washington baltimore and 
philadelphia to build on the states traditional bases of boston and 
new york 
more manmade snow is being poured on slopes earlier than ever a 
2yearold eastman kodak inc product called snomax allows snow to 
be made at temperatures 4 degrees to 8 degrees warmer than before 
as high as freezing 
thanks to more sophisticated snowmaking camp said more than 50 
of the 72 public ski areas in the sixstate new england region were 
open last weekend a quantum leap over previous years 
said conniff the technology thats come along has taken a lot 
of the risk out of the business in the last three or four years 
the onset of cold weather also has encouraged area ski officials 
hopeful that singledigit temperatures will persuade city dwellers 
to head for the slopes 
the most important thing this cold weather has given us is an 
unprecedented jump on snowmaking efforts said david zemel 
general manager of the powder ridge ski resort in middlefield conn 
more slopes are opening faster than ive ever seen in the seven 
years ive been here 
