belgiums central bank boosted all key 
banking interest rates by 025 percentage points wednesday 
reflecting the growing trend toward higher rates in the 
international markets 
the belgian national bank wednesday said the discount rate was 
raised to 75 percent and the lombard rate to 775 percent 
the discount rate is the interest the central bank charges on 
loans to member commercial banksthe lombard rate is what the banks 
are charged for supplemental borrowings in which securities are used 
as collateral 
the national bank had announced earlier it was raising one two 
and threemonth treasury bills 
the threemonth rate considered the most important in belgian 
banking was raised to 74 percent from 715 percent the onemonth 
rate to 735 from 71 percent and the twomonth rate to 74 from 
715 percent 
all the moves take effect on thursday 
the national bank said the rate changes came in recognition of 
the recent evolution of interest rates on the international 
markets 
