editors note with the makeit or breakit season in full swing 
for the nations retailers the associated press takes an inside 
look at how two stores are handling the holiday rush in sidebyside 
stories from new york city and grand rapids mich 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
marcia massa used to buy 280 sweaters to stock 
her small manhattan boutique osidi but her expectations about 
holiday sales this year are slightly less ambitious 
id shake if i took that in said the store owner explaining 
how the long slump in apparel sales has colored her inventory 
decisions for the season 
while she did order a handful of 400 outfits with customers 
shopping for new years eve in mind the shops fashion statement 
this christmas is stylish yet inexpensive 
i think theres a big economic problem in the city said mrs 
massa during a reporters visit to osidi in gramercy park south and 
to the east of midtown manhattan 
but she also predicted the season is going to be ok i have 
no doubt about that 
when you think of shopping in manhattan big stores like macys 
or bloomingdales come to mind or on a smaller scale the scores of 
trendy shops on madison and columbus avenues 
osidi is nothing like any of those retailers it is a small 
neighborhood store that caters to women who live in what is a 
largely middleclass area 
the bulk of mrs massas business comes from regular customers 
many of whom she knows on a firstname basis and who dont like the 
big stores 
they periodically stop by just to see whats new and maybe chat 
and have a cup of coffee with the owner an outgoing woman who 
obviously loves what shes doing 
the store sells casual clothing and outfits that could be worn to 
work or to parties sweaters at osidi go for 48 to 70 and two 
and threepiece wool jersey outfits range from about 220 to the low 
300s at this time of the year there are a number of party dresses 
for about 200 
osidi does a lot of business in accessories silver antique and 
costume jewelry scarves lingerie belts and pocketbooks these 
lowticket items have been the boutiques biggest sellers so far 
this season 
holiday sales at osidi the stores name comes from the nickname 
of one of mrs massas friends have been erratic this year 
the friday after thanksgiving in contrast to the mob scene 
uptown at macys bloomingdales and other big stores osidi was 
quiet but mrs massa was unperturbed although that day was the 
traditional start of the christmas shopping season it has never 
been a big day at her store 
business picked up over the following weekend but sales have 
ebbed and flowed since then along with mrs massas outlook 
when volume picked up several days into december she was pleased 
but realistic its nothing like it should be 
like most other stores across the country osidi has had to lower 
its expectations because of the nearly 2yearold slump in retail 
spending mrs massa who has been a clothing retailer or 
manufacturer for more than 20 years said the 14 months since 
october 1987 have been the worst retail season shes seen 
she remembers painfully well oct 19 of last year the day of 
the stock market crash osidi took in 30 in sales 
since then her business has changed drastically some of osidis 
customers who included stockbrokers lost their jobs others 
became very wary they think twice is the way mrs massa puts 
it 
that customers not there any longer she said of the women 
who used to spend freely 
these days she says it is her regular customers who thank god 
keep me in business 
she knows shes not alone that other retailers have had the same 
troubles over the past year and shes heard via the merchant 
grapevine that their christmas season is going slowly 
my suppliers say everyones crying she said 
mrs massa went into the last two weeks of the season complaining 
that no one seemed to be in the christmas spirit yet she still 
expected things to turn out all right if not great 
normally were a late store she said explaining that the 
bulk of her christmas business comes in the final week from 
lastminute shoppers and people who couldnt find what they wanted 
anywhere else or who couldnt contend with the uptown crowds 
on the very last day of the season christmas eve she expects to 
see mostly men buying a lot of jewelry 
will she be satisfied at the end if and when those eleventhhour 
shoppers come through 
no the numbers just arent there she said and added no 
matter what you do people arent going to spend money 
</TEXT>
