the agriculture issue is not solved he warned theres obviously 
jeopardy to the entire uruguay round 
the controversy stems from a us demand that all members of the 
general agreement on tariffs and trade gatt abolish their farm 
supports which distort trade on the world market the eec under 
strong pressure from its large rural population advocates reduction 
in subsidies but not elimination 
were on the side of the angels on this issue yeutter said 
and everyone including our european allies knows this 
the united states contends that elimination of farm supports will 
lower government expenditure and ease the burden on consumers and 
taxpayers around the world 
